

PAGER                 Environmental Variable                PAGER




Specify Output Filter

PPAAGGEERR=``_c_o_m_m_a_n_d _o_p_t_i_o_n_s''

The environmental  variable PPAAGGEERR directs programs  such as mmssggss,
mmaaiill  and  others  to  ``pipe''  their  output into  the  _c_o_m_m_a_n_d
specified as the value  of PPAAGGEERR. For example, the following sets
up /bbiinn/ssccaatt  as the desired  output filter and  passes a command
line option to it to specify that the output screen has 20 lines.


        export PAGER="exec /bin/scat -l20"


